# Feature completion — CHANGELOG and version

When you **finish a user-facing feature** (or a meaningful bug-fix batch), do not
stop at code and tests. Also update release metadata before considering the task
done.

Skip version bumps only for trivial chores with no product impact (typos,
formatting-only, comment-only) unless the user explicitly asks for a release.

## 1. Update `CHANGELOG.md`

Follow [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.1.0/):

- Add bullets under `## [Unreleased]` in the right subsection:
  `Added`, `Changed`, `Fixed`, `Removed`, `Security`.
- Write user-facing, concise bullets (what changed and why it matters).
- Mention new test counts when the suite grew materially (e.g. **1549** total).
- When bumping the version, **move** `[Unreleased]` entries into a new dated
  section `## [X.Y.Z] - YYYY-MM-DD`, then leave a fresh empty `[Unreleased]`.
- Update the compare links at the bottom of `CHANGELOG.md` for the new tag.

## 2. Bump the app version (SemVer)

Canonical source: `Version.props` (`VersionPrefix`, `AssemblyVersion`,
`FileVersion`). While the app is pre-1.0 (`0.x.y`):

| Change type | Bump |
|-------------|------|
| New user-visible capability, export/import format, template set, UI flow | **MINOR** (`0.2.1` → `0.3.0`) |
| Bug fix, parser/export correction, CI/test-only fix shipped as maintenance | **PATCH** (`0.2.1` → `0.2.2`) |

Keep `AssemblyVersion` / `FileVersion` in sync with the release (e.g. `0.2.2.0`).

## 3. Mirror the version everywhere

After editing `Version.props`, update these to the same `VersionPrefix`:

1. `package.json` → `"version"`
2. `README.md` → app badge `badge/app-X.Y.Z-blue`
3. `src/ReVitae/app.manifest` → `assemblyIdentity version="X.Y.Z.0"`

Do not duplicate version constants in C# source; the UI reads `AppVersion`.

## 4. Validate

Run:

```bash
./scripts/verify-version.sh
npm run lint
```

Fix any drift before handing work back to the user.

## Example (feature → `0.2.1` → `0.3.0`)

1. `CHANGELOG.md`: move Unreleased bullets into `## [0.3.0] - 2026-05-21`.
2. `Version.props`: `VersionPrefix` / `AssemblyVersion` / `FileVersion` → `0.3.0` / `0.3.0.0`.
3. `package.json`, README badge, `app.manifest` → `0.3.0`.
4. `./scripts/verify-version.sh` passes.

Do **not** create Git tags or GitHub Releases unless the user asks.
